statement:
[**The Gelfand-Naimark representation theorem is as follows:**]{}

[**Theorem 1.1**]{}

[*Every $C^*$-algebra is isometrically isomorphic to a norm closed
\*-subalgebra ${\mathbb{B}}_{nc}({\mathord{\mathcal{H}}})$ of an algebra
${\mathbb{B}}({\mathord{\mathcal{H}}})$ of bounded operators on some
Hilbert space ${\mathord{\mathcal{H}}}$. In particular, every finite
dimensional $C^*$-algebra is isomorphic to a direct sum of matrix
algebras.*]{}
